				.text
					p Flow is a new social club and teaching center being built to strengthen and expand the acumen, power, and <strong>thriving of women, globally</strong>. In sumptuous physical space, we provide a gathering point for inspired connections. With and tools and services, we support our members’ financial literacy, total wellbeing and community impact.
					p Our offerings will range from service-oriented and technological conveniences to capacity building educational experiences.
					.more
						p Membership is available to self-proclaimed women, age 18+. We support the flourishing of community through a commitment to serving women's needs. Visitors and guests of any gender are warmly welcomed on specific days, community events, and tailored programs.
						p As a global club with a long-term vision and strong social and ethical commitments, we prioritize access and impact through a robust and anonymously sponsored membership fund. In the next decade we envision Flow chapters spanning six continents linking millions of women to each other, to local and to global causes.


					.more-button More

			.parallax-window.r1
			.text-block
				.text 
					p In addition to providing beautiful space for our members, we work with programming <strong>partners who serve women</strong>, including community leaders, creative mavens, scholars, private coaches, career and financial experts, and spiritual luminaries. Offering a spectrum of services through our programming partners opens the door to access, knowledge, and options for the Flow community. In partnerships, we select for experience, responsibility, talent, and authenticity.
					.more
						p Flow will also offer discovery tools and foundational programs for our members who wish to focus and strengthen their capabilities and skills. We collaborate with each member as she nourishes and unleashes her own abilities through our workshops, sisterhoods, and mentoring.
					.more-button More


			.parallax-window.r2
			.text-block
				.text
					p Flow Global, Inc. is created with <strong>principle and purpose</strong> at its core. Our organizational structure is a hybrid non-profit/for-profit enterprise.				
					.more
						p Demonstrating societal contribution and impact, inclusive and aligned with personal thriving, is the highest aspiration of our organization.

						p We uphold a stewardship model over an ownership model and actively work toward healthy financial self-sufficiency over dependence and debt.
						p Flow Global, Inc. does not exist in order to make individuals wealthy at the expense of its goals, mission or members.
						p <strong>We value:</strong>

						p 
							li Thoughtful, heartfelt action.
							li Diversity of ideas and people.
							li Clear lines of responsibility.
							li A joyous, creative and soulful work environment.

						h3 Team
						p <strong>Mirran Raphaely</strong> feels a relentless calling to launch Flow Global. In her sixteen years helping to build the renowned and forerunning Dr. Hauschka Skin Care brand, and specifically seven as its US CEO, she developed ideas, methods, products and teams that view the world differently. Mirran celebrates the spirit of human striving, our sacred natural world and the magic of organizations working passionately to make a difference for the planet and her inhabitants.

						p <strong>Bec Chapin</strong> creates space for people to thrive in community. She has spent the past 5 years as a professional builder and executive, using pre-fab and sustainable construction as a lever for change in the world. Bec is an alumna of Mount Holyoke women’s college and Bainbridge Graduate Institute, as well as a sailor, a certified marine engineer, and a third degree black belt in Tae Kwon Do. This foundation has built for her the perspective, awareness and self-assurance to nurture the best in humanity.
						
						p <strong>Stephanie Ciancio</strong> envisions a new norm of women smiling at each other on sidewalks, knowing even before they’ve met that they’re in on something revolutionary. In addition to a BA from McGill University in Humanistic Studies, she holds an MBA in Sustainability from Presidio Graduate School and has worked with numerous urban-focused startups as a team manager and community builder. 

						p <strong>Troy Carter</strong> is a joy-filled soul and explorer, manifesting his utopian dreams for human culture throughout the world. He holds a degree in economics from Stanford University, and envisions a paradigm shift in the balance of feminine and masculine energy, economic livelihoods that support profound meaning and self-realization, and the evolution of human communication. After 4,000 years of excessively yang society, he finds it appropriate that the midwife for Flow is a man.


